meta {
  name: 6.1 Best games - typed POJO
  type: http
  seq: 1
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/games
  body: json
  auth: inherit
}

headers {
  Content-Type: application/json
}

body:json {
  {
    "genre": "open-world RPG"
  }
}

settings {
  encodeUrl: true
}

docs {
  # Structured-output demo (no RAG)

  Ask for the 3 best open-world RPGs. The AiService method returns a Java record
  (GameChart -> List<Game>), so the model is forced to answer as JSON matching that
  shape, and Quarkus deserializes it for you.

  Expected: clean JSON like
    { "genre": "open-world RPG",
      "games": [ { "name": "...", "publisher": "...",
                   "metacriticScore": 93, "releaseYear": 2015 }, ... ] }

  No manual JSON parsing anywhere — the endpoint returns the typed object and
  quarkus-rest serializes it back to JSON.

  Note: gpt-4o-mini (default profile) is rock-solid here. On local Ollama with a
  small model the JSON is usually fine but can occasionally wobble — if it does,
  re-run, or use the OpenAI profile for this one.
}
